uratorName":"Apple Music Hip-Hop","description":{"standard":"Kanye West started out as thefirst backpacker with a Benz, a genius producer with a deep throwback streak, lacing hardcore rappers and R&B playas with soulful Golden Age beats. Grabbing the mic from his heroes, Yeezy immediately unlocked his inner swag, blurring the lines between audacious pop superstar, musical visionary, and intensely intimate MC. While he drops more outrageous boasts-per-minute than just about anyone, Kanye's rhymes mix deadly seriousness with over-the-top silliness, injecting even his most political and personal bars with razor-sharp punchlines. His sound is just as kaleidoscopic, tracking a restless creative mind as he flips dusty jazz loops, soaring EDM riffs, angelic gospel harmonies, furious rock drumming, and so much more. He'll rip up your heart on haunting slow jams like \u201cLove Lockdown,\u201d pump your adrenaline with ferocious bangers like \u201cBlack Skinhead,\u201d and have you going rhyme for rhyme on all-time anthems like\u201cGold Digger.\u201d","short":"A journey into the unpredictable mind of a hip-hop visionary."},"lastModifiedDate":"2017-11-06T19:19:31Z","playlistType":"editorial","playParams":{"id":"pl.f8b1e707c4d242298a27c75534e4218d","kind":"playlist"}}},{"id":"pl.325add15d45444df9535c07f65424764","type":"playlists","href":"\/v1\/catalog\/us\/playlists\/pl.325add15d45444df9535c07f65424764","attributes":{"url":"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/playlist\/kanye-west-next-steps\/pl.325add15d45444df9535c07f65424764","artwork":{"width":4320,"height":1080,"url":"https:\/\/is3-ssl.mzstatic.com\/image\/thumb\/Features118\/v4\/28\/bd\/db\/28bddb35-7c44-72fb-5dd7-1fe0c07b539e\/source\/{w}x{h}bb.jpg","bgColor":"121212","textColor1":"ffffff","textColor2":"d9d9d9","textColor3":"cfcfcf","textColor4":"b1b1b1"},"name":"KanyeWest: Next Steps","curatorName":"Apple Music Hip-Hop","description":{"standard":"Kanye West approaches his album cuts with the same meticulousness he puts into his singles. The results are often even more daring\u2014perhaps because of freedom from radio constraints\u2014with extensive music bridges (\u201cDevil in a New Dress\u201d) and drastic sonic changes (\u201cGone\u201d).","short":"Kanye West approaches his album cuts with the same meticulousness as his singles."},"lastModifiedDate":"2017-11-06T19:23:35Z","playlistType":"editorial","playParams":{"id":"pl.325add15d45444df9535c07f65424764","kind":"playlist"}}},{"id":"pl.ecb07a84b0164c1e99a95a2e416e4926","type":"playlists","href":"\/v1\/catalog\/us\/playlists\/pl.ecb07a84b0164c1e99a95a2e416e4926","attributes":{"url":"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/playlist\/partners-in-rhyme-jay-z-and-kanye-west\/pl.ecb07a84b0164c1e99a95a2e416e4926","artwork":{"width":4320,"height":1080,"url":"https:\/\/is5-ssl.mzstatic.com\/image\/thumb\/Features62\/v4\/bd\/94\/21\/bd9421ce-3b4b-c4bc-3221-59cb29d3620f\/source\/{w}x{h}bb.jpg","bgColor":"ecebea","textColor1":"0b0404","textColor2":"3c2f18","textColor3":"383232","textColor4":"5f5442"},"name":"Partners In Rhyme: Jay Z and Kanye West","curatorName":"Apple Music Hip-Hop","description":{"standard":"Jay Z and Kanye West initially had a rapper\/producer relationship but the pair quickly began rhyming side by side. Yeezy provided the chorus to Scarface's \"Guess Who's Back?\" featuring JAY Z in 2002 and appeared on Hov's \"The Bounce\" later that year. Hov guested on West's first two LPs, The College Dropout and Late Registration. The two eventually joined forces to issue the epic Watch the Throne in 2011.","short":"Watch the Throne\u2014and thensome."},"lastModifiedDate":"2015-04-11T16:19:24Z","playlistType":"editorial","playParams":{"id":"pl.ecb07a84b0164c1e99a95a2e416e4926","kind":"playlist"}}},{"id":"pl.16fbf943d0334e75937c90523e2d96e9","type":"playlists","href":"\/v1\/catalog\/us\/playlists\/pl.16fbf943d0334e75937c90523e2d96e9","attributes":{"url":"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/playlist\/kanye-west-r-b-productions\/pl.16fbf943d0334e75